definition: lit. each color and each form (idiom)/diverse/various/all kinds of

sentences.english: They are strictly vegetarian and eat all manner of deep fried food.
sentences.chinese: 他们是严格的食素者，吃各种各样的油炸食品。

sentences.english: Residential carpenters erect all types of homes, including apartments and townhouses.
sentences.chinese: 住宅木匠会建造各式各样的房屋，例如公寓和市政厅。

sentences.english: A bowl-shaped desert island inhabited by a variety of monsters.
sentences.chinese: 狭长的沙漠岛，息居着各种各样的怪兽。

sentences.english: So get all sources of sweets, deserts and sugar out of your house.
sentences.chinese: 把各种各样的糖果，甜点和其他糖移出你的房间。

sentences.english: All kinds of things go on in these baths.
sentences.chinese: 浴室会发生各种各样事情。

sentences.english: People catch all kinds of infections in the winter.
sentences.chinese: 人们在冬天易患各种各样的传染病。

sentences.english: So, Langer applied for various jobs in education, but with very little success.
sentences.chinese: 所以兰格申请了各种各样的教育工作，但是成就有限。

sentences.english: These eave tiles are carved with many animal pictures.
sentences.chinese: 这些瓦当上都刻有各种各样的动物图案。

sentences.english: That the man of God may be complete, fully equipped for every good work.
sentences.chinese: 叫属神的人得以完备，为着各样的善工，装备齐全。

sentences.english: and all kinds of science things you can play with, so.
sentences.chinese: 还有各种各样的科技产品你可以玩。

sentences.english: The town offers many shops and cafes and a wide variety of entertainment.
sentences.chinese: 镇上有许多商店和咖啡馆以及各种各样的文娱活动。

sentences.english: Indexes cover all sorts of subjects.
sentences.chinese: 索引涉及各式各样的主题。
我们有各种各样的光线。

sentences.english: All sorts of fine-sounding schemes were brought forward.
sentences.chinese: 各种各样动听的计划给提了出来。

sentences.english: It's like a watch – there are various levels of intricacy .
sentences.chinese: 这就像手表，有各式各样的复杂程度。

sentences.english: Peole don't want to grow up because of the various pressures and non-freedom.
sentences.chinese: 人们不想长大，因为各种各样的压力和不自由。
